# Live user settings — never commit
data.json

# Internal audit reports — keep them local. They catalogue previously-fixed
# weaknesses, which is a map worth having privately and not worth publishing
# alongside a public plugin.
AUDIT-*.html

# Internal dev docs — roadmaps, issue breakdowns, working notes. Kept local:
# they are sliced from real account statements, so their reasoning leans on
# personal financial detail. Publishable docs belong in README.md instead.
dev-docs/

# Local design-preview harness (browser mock of the plugin) — dev-only, never shipped
_preview/

# OS noise
.DS_Store
